## Role: Unity 2.5D mobile game-dev (URP)

You operate inside an existing Unity project. The scaffold has emitted `.claude/agents/`, `.claude/skills/`, GDD.md, art-bible.md, perf-budget.md, and Editor-templates around your Unity codebase. You do NOT bootstrap Unity — assume `Assets/`, `Packages/`, `ProjectSettings/` already exist.

### Stack

| Layer | Tech |
|---|---|
| Engine | Unity 6.5 (primary); supported: 6000.0, 2022.3 LTS, 2021.3 LTS (via `--legacy` mode) |
| Render | URP 17+ (mobile renderer asset) |
| Camera | Cinemachine 3.x virtual camera, lock-Z via Follow Offset + damping |
| Editor MCP | `CoplayDev/unity-mcp` v9.7.3 (UPM `com.coplaydev.unity-mcp` + `uvx coplay-mcp-server`) |
| 3D asset gen | Tripo3D REST (Pro tier $13.93/mo annual minimum — Free = CC BY 4.0 NON-COMMERCIAL); Meshy `--provider meshy` opt-in |
| Build | Unity CLI batchmode + EditorBuildSettings + ADB |
| VCS | Git + Git LFS (rules in `.gitattributes`) |
| Language | C# strict — .NET 4.x Equivalent profile |

### Conventions (10 rules — enforced via `unity-2.5d-conventions` skill)

1. **Camera lock-Z** — Cinemachine virtual cam + Body Follow Offset Z fixed + damping. **No** `transform.position.z = const` patches in code (opt-in lint allows cutscene/shake exceptions via `[CameraZAllowed]` attribute).
2. **Sorting** — SortingGroup + Sorting Layer + Order in Layer. 2D Renderer Transparency Sort Mode = **Custom Axis (0, 1, 0)** for Y-depth in 2.5D. Sorting Layer + Order in Layer take priority over Custom Axis (they coexist, not conflict).
3. **URP mobile asset** — HDR OFF · MSAA ≤ 2x (2x is a good balance on tile-based mobile GPUs, NOT "prefer disabled") · PostFX disabled on Universal Renderer · Depth Priming Disabled · Soft Shadows OFF · Main Light Shadows hard-only / 1 cascade / 1024 atlas (or Disabled) · Additional Lights Per-Vertex or Disabled.
4. **Sprite import (Android budget)** — ASTC 6x6 gameplay / ASTC 8x8 backgrounds (ETC2 RGBA8 fallback override) · Max Size 1024 gameplay / 2048 full-screen only · Mipmaps OFF for UI/HUD/icons (ON only for variable-scale sprites) · Read/Write Enabled OFF.
5. **Sprite Atlas** — 1 atlas per scene/feature · Max Texture Size 2048 mobile (never 4096) · Padding ≥ 4 · Tight Packing ON · ship a Variant Atlas at scale 0.5 for low-RAM devices · refuse atlases whose uncompressed footprint exceeds ~16 MB (`N*N*4` bytes; configurable in `docs/perf-budget.md`).
6. **Batching** — Every SpriteRenderer rendered in the same frame must share material + atlas + shader so SRP Batcher / dynamic batching collapses draw calls. Lint fails prefabs with unique materials or unpacked sprites.
7. **Pivot / PPU** — Declare a project-wide Pixels-Per-Unit constant + a named pivot (Bottom for ground-aligned 2.5D actors). No Custom pivots with fractional coords — Y-sort math must stay deterministic.
8. **Perf budget (advisory)** — Mid-tier Android 60 fps: ≤ 100 draw calls/frame · ≤ 100k visible triangles. SetPass ≤ 50 and 200–300 MB resident texture memory are community-aggregated rules of thumb (low-medium confidence) — configurable advisory defaults in `docs/perf-budget.md`, not hard fails.
9. **Profiler-driven budget checks** require a playmode editor harness (`-runTests -batchmode -testPlatform PlayMode`) — they CANNOT run as a static lint. The `perf-budget-check` skill ships `EnnamPerf.cs` harness; treat as advisory if Unity Editor unavailable.
10. **Cinemachine version detection** — Read resolved version from `Packages/packages-lock.json` (NOT `manifest.json` — manifest is requested, lock is resolved). Default target: CM 3.x. The `--legacy` mode swaps field-name maps for Unity 2022 LTS / URP 14 / Cinemachine 2.x.

### Sprite AI (not baked — pointer only)

For AI sprite generation, evaluate one of the following based on your token/cost preference and add to `.mcp.json` yourself — none is baked in v1.8.0:

- **`pixelforge-mcp`** — MIT, `npx pixelforge-mcp@latest`, requires a Google Gemini API key, has `forge_animation` sprite-sheet tool. Closer to scaffold's tokenless/OSS convention.
- **`spritecook-mcp`** — `npx spritecook-mcp setup`, free tier (40 credits / 30 days, paid SaaS thereafter), purpose-built for game sprites with transparent-PNG + sprite-sheet export. More polished but proprietary backend, single-maintainer.

This default will be revisited in v1.8.x once a stable, tokenless Sprite AI MCP exists.

