### Workflow (8 phases — game-specific extension of the 7-phase shared workflow)

| # | Phase | Skill / Command | Skip if | Output |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Understand | `superpowers:brainstorming` | bug with clear repro | GDD-aligned spec in `docs/superpowers/specs/` |
| 2 | Plan | `superpowers:writing-plans` | single-file C# fix | Implementation plan + success criteria |
| 3 | Isolate | `superpowers:using-git-worktrees` | hotfix | Worktree (Unity `Library/` shared via junction/symlink — Unity does not handle two checkouts of `Library/` cleanly) |
| 4 | Implement (closed-loop) | `superpowers:test-driven-development` + `superpowers:executing-plans` | trivial | **Loop: edit script → Unity MCP `compile_scripts` → `read_console` → fix → repeat until clean.** No commit while console has error-level messages. |
| 5 | Verify (auto) | `superpowers:verification-before-completion` | NEVER | Compile clean + console no error + PlayMode tests pass + `unity-2.5d-conventions` lint green + `perf-budget-check` advisory |
| 6 | **Content Gates (HUMAN)** | `/unity-content-gate` command | NEVER for feature work | 1 PR comment with 4 checkboxes: **Design** (GDD.md compliance) · **Art** (art-bible.md compliance) · **Feel** (manual playtest) · **Perf** (budget §3 #8 met). Each gate signed by a human reviewer before Phase 7. |
| 7 | Review | `superpowers:requesting-code-review` | docs-only | Reviewer agent feedback addressed |
| 8 | Complete | `superpowers:finishing-a-development-branch` | — | PR merged or completion option presented |

**Phase 6 gate template** (paste into PR body):

```markdown
## Content Gates (Phase 6)
- [ ] **Design** — change aligns with GDD.md sections cited
- [ ] **Art** — assets conform to art-bible.md (style, palette, forbidden list)
- [ ] **Feel** — manual playtest passed (link to recording or notes)
- [ ] **Perf** — `perf-budget-check` run; metrics within budget (`docs/perf-budget.md`)
```
