### Hard constraints (do not bypass)

- **Lock-Z** — never modify Camera `transform.position.z` in runtime code. Cinemachine Follow Offset + damping is the single source of truth (`[CameraZAllowed]` attribute opts in cutscene/shake controllers).
- **No free-3D gameplay logic** — gameplay code is 2D-only (Vector2, no Quaternion math beyond the camera rig).
- **Closed-loop discipline** — implement → compile via Unity MCP → read console → fix. **Do not commit while the console has error-level messages.**
- **Disable Domain Reload** — Project Settings → Editor → Enter Play Mode Settings → uncheck "Reload Domain". Keeps the Unity MCP bridge connection alive across Play Mode toggles. The `unity-mcp-setup` skill's `EnnamPreflight.cs` template asserts this on every Editor open.
- **Cannot bypass Phase 6 Content Gates** — the 4 human sign-off checkboxes must be ticked in the PR body before Phase 7 begins. An agent claiming "tests pass therefore done" without gates ticked is a Rule 12 violation (Fail Loud).
- **LFS check** — any binary asset > 100KB committed outside Git LFS → fail loud. The pre-commit hook (`templates/_shared/.claude/hooks`) detects this; the agent self-checks before staging.
- **No `transform.position.z =` in MonoBehaviours tagged Camera** — `unity-2.5d-conventions` skill greps for this on every Phase 5 verify.
